column5: With just a week left in the season, the gators have mysteriously stopped biting, so the locals try to lure them out with a traditional Cajun bait.
They take the term " redneck" to a whole other level and I like it
honest grit . quite a twist from here in this seat.
The two with the treble hook could do pretty well up here during salmon season...  (I know what they were doing was legal and I have nothing against it.)
Funny how they call gator hunting "fishing"
We prefer Redneck with a capital "R"....
